    "ideation": "The studio microphone is not a passive object; it is an active listener and a channel for voice. The animation treats the face as the transducer itself. The eyes represent the recording indicators: starting as a warm 'standby' amber, then transitioning to a focused 'on-air' red. The mouth is the literal audio waveform. I've designed the sequence to mimic the behavior of a voice track being recorded: starting with a low noise floor, hitting a sudden peak (the 'loud' signal), experiencing 'clipping' (the gritted high-frequency mouth), and then settling into a clean, normalized signal. The color moves from gold to signal-red to high-fidelity cyan.",
